cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this dataset, code, or benchmark, please cite the accompanying paper as well as the dataset deposit."
title: "RegConflict: A Cross-Jurisdictional Benchmark for Regulatory Conflict Detection"
type: dataset
abstract: >-
  RegConflict is a benchmark for detecting conflicts between regulatory regimes
  across jurisdictions in financial regulation. It comprises a four-class
  typology of regulatory conflicts (structural, operationally resolvable,
  interpretive, recurring friction), approximately 250 expert-labelled conflict
  pairs across six jurisdictional sources (Australia, the European Union,
  Singapore, FATF, BIS, IOSCO), a curated multi-jurisdictional regulatory
  corpus of 247 source documents released under a documented per-source
  licensing framework, and baseline results spanning random predictors,
  zero-shot prompted LLMs at two parameter scales, and a supervised fine-tuned
  encoder.
